ing-nasa-234803320.html">包括联邦政府）</a>使用该应用程序的方法。 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.cnn.com/2023/01/16/tech/tiktok-state-restrictions/index.html">现在，33 个州（跨党派）都限制在政府拥有的技术上使用 TikTok</a> 。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>随着考虑全面禁止 TikTok 和其他与中国政府相关的应用程序的立法不断重新浮出水面，字节<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/can-tiktok-convince-the-us-its-not-a-national-security-threat-173030115.html">跳动努力证明它不会对国家安全构成威胁</a>。 TikTok首席执行官Shou Chew <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/heres-what-tiktoks-ceo-told-congress-about-the-apps-ties-to-china-and-teen-safety-201657076.html">甚至在国会面前作证</a>重申“字节跳动不是中国代理人”。</p><p>截至发稿时，纽约市技术与创新办公室尚未回应置评请求。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-bans-tiktok-for-government-employees-174806575.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-bans-tiktok-for-government-employees-174806575.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0cfde25f-77e6-47df-b88a-5441988f8f96</guid><dc:creator>凯蒂·马龙</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 16 Aug 2023 17:48:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692208112</ingested><modified> 2023-08-16T17:48:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Katie Malone]]></category><media:content height="3074" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7939c890-3c59-11ee-b7fc-d1c7d0c6138a" width="4611"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:c